Details:
“Krishi Input Anudan Yojana” launched by the Department of Agriculture, Bihar, is designed to offer agricultural input subsidies in areas affected by rising water levels in rivers such as the Ganga and Kosi. Assistance are provided for crop damage more than 33% caused by heavy rainfall and flooding.
&lt;br&gt;
The scheme aims to provide agricultural input subsidies in affected areas due to the rise in water levels of rivers like Ganga and Kosi and flood-related crop damage from heavy rainfall.

The &amp;quot;Mukhyamantri Rajya Krishi Vikas Yojana&amp;quot; is introduced by the Sugarcane Development and Sugar Industry, Govt of Uttarakhand, which aims to achieve holistic development of the agriculture and allied sectors, focusing on improved sugarcane cultivation. Through this scheme, grants for sugarcane seed production, certification, field demonstrations, transportation, agricultural machinery, seed price payments, pest/disease and weed control, and distribution of micro nutrients and bio-fertilizers are provided to sugarcane farmers, progressive farmers, co-operative sugarcane societies, and progressive sugarcane farmers engaged in improved sugarcane cultivation. The scheme is implemented by the Sugarcane Department and research centres like G.B. Pant University of Agriculture and Technology, Pantnagar.
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;br&gt;

<br>
The scheme aims to enhance sugarcane cultivation through grants for seed production, machinery, pest control, and training. Through this scheme, various financial grants and support services are provided to sugarcane farmers and related agricultural entities.

